ActOther Than Statutory Authority
SubjectOrder Respecting the Interim Federal Health Program, 2012
PrecisOrder Respecting the INTERIM FEDERAL HEALTH PROGRAM, 2012 to (1) repeal Order in Council P.C. 157-11/848 of June 20, 1957; (2) provide either health care coverage or public health or public safety health care coverage, on a temporary basis, to persons including: refugee claimants, protected persons, persons detained under the Immigration and Refugee Protection Act, and rejected refugee claimants; (3) provide coverage that is not more generous than what Canadians receive through government-funded benefit programs; and (4) protect public health or public safety.
